{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:30:55.287991+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a comprehensive summary of how to run and build this React admin app locally and for different environments.\n\n---\n\n## How to Run and Build This React Admin App\n\n### Prerequisites & Initial Setup\n\nThe project uses **Vite + React + TypeScript + MUI**, managed with **Yarn**. The `Taskfile.yaml` defines an `init` task that bootstraps everything:\n\n```bash\n# Install Task runner (https://taskfile.dev), then:\ntask init\n```\n\nThis does three things:\n1. Installs global tools (`conventional-changelog-cli`, `standard-version`, `commitizen`)\n2. **Copies `envs/.env.local` → `.env`** at the project root (this is critical — it's what Vite reads)\n3. Runs `yarn install`\n\nAlternatively, you can do it manually:\n```bash\ncp envs/.env.local .env\nyarn install\n```\n\n---\n\n### Environment Files\n\nThe project stores environment configs in `envs/`:\n\n| File | `NODE_ENV` | Purpose | API Base URL | Port |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `.env.local` | `local` | Local development | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` | `10086` |\n| `.env.stg` | `stg` | Staging | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` | `10086` |\n| `.env.prod` | `prod` | Production | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` | *(empty)* |\n\nThe Vite config (`vite.config.ts`) loads environment variables via a custom `dotenv.config()` call: it first checks for a `.env` file at the project root; if none exists, it falls back to `envs/.env.${NODE_ENV}`.\n\n---\n\n### Running Locally (Development)\n\n**Local environment (default):**\n```bash\nyarn dev\n```\n- Runs `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host`\n- Loads `envs/.env.local` (or root `.env` if present)\n- Starts the Vite dev server on port **10086** with hot module replacement (HMR)\n- `--host` exposes it on the local network\n\n**Staging environment:**\n```bash\nyarn dev:stg\n```\n- Runs `cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite`\n- Loads `envs/.env.stg`\n- Same dev server, but pointed at the staging mock API\n\n---\n\n### Building for Different Environments\n\n| Command | What it does | Env file loaded |\n|---|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | `vite build --mode prod` | `envs/.env.prod` |\n| `yarn build:stg` | `cross-env vite build --mode test` | `envs/.env.stg`* |\n| `yarn build:prod` | `cross-env vite build --mode production` | `envs/.env.prod`* |\n\nAll builds output to `dist/`.\n\n> \\* For `build:stg` and `build:prod`, the mode string becomes `process.env.NODE_ENV` in Vite's config context, which the custom dotenv loader uses to pick the corresponding file from `envs/`.\n\n---\n\n### Previewing a Production Build\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n```\n- Runs `vite preview --host`\n- Serves the contents of `dist/` on a local preview server (similar port behavior as dev)\n\n---\n\n### Docker Build & Serve\n\nThe `Dockerfile` provides a multi-stage Docker build:\n\n1. **Builder stage** (Node LTS Alpine): copies source, runs `yarn` and `yarn build`\n2. **Serve stage** (Nginx Alpine): copies the built `dist/` and a custom `nginx.conf`\n\n```bash\ndocker build -t vite-react-ts-admin .\ndocker run -p 8080:80 vite-react-ts-admin\n```\n\nThe `nginx.conf` serves the SPA with a `try_files` fallback to `index.html` (required for client-side routing via React Router), and also has a dedicated `/admin` location block.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Reference\n\n| Goal | Command |\n|---|---|\n| First-time setup | `task init` |\n| Start local dev server | `yarn dev` |\n| Start staging dev server | `yarn dev:stg` |\n| Production build | `yarn build` |\n| Staging build | `yarn build:stg` |\n| Preview built output | `yarn serve` |\n| Lint | `yarn lint` |\n| Fix lint issues | `yarn fix` |\n| Docker build & run | `docker build -t admin . && docker run -p 8080:80 admin` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 2348, "prompt_tokens": 8529, "total_tokens": 10877, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 1320, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7936, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007626808, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001052408, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00065744}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780871430-e94f8bjjFVAqeKVv8SA8", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea435-7f54-7953-af28-a5c93d53ff86-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8529, "output_tokens": 2348, "total_tokens": 10877, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7936}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1320}}}}]}}}
